Marshal V2 / Rollout Review Packet
Generated for colleague review on 2026-06-03.

Purpose
-------
Please review the current Marshal public contract and the latest finite cleanup
state. The important question is whether the Marshal boundary, public tool
surface, rollout handoff model, and operator response vocabulary are now
coherent enough to commit as a stable checkpoint.

Core operative model
--------------------
Lattice proves.
Runtime executes.
Marshal coordinates, validates, delegates, records, and explains.
Cajtucu paper-executes replay mechanics under Runtime replay.

Public Marshal tools
--------------------
The public Marshal surface is exactly:

  hero.marshal.status
  hero.marshal.prepare
  hero.marshal.rollout
  hero.marshal.inspect

Short meanings:

  status   = what Marshal can see
  prepare  = how one Lattice target can move next
  rollout  = how one completed Runtime job can be replayed through environment
  inspect  = what existing evidence says

Recent implemented roadmap slices
---------------------------------
V2.2a/V2.2b:
  - rollout is now a first-class public tool, not prepare intent=rollout.
  - rollout requested_mode is plan|execute.
  - legacy rollout requested_mode=dry_run is rejected.
  - legacy rollout prepare_only is rejected.
  - rollout requires:
      rollout_id
      rollout_attempt_id
      idempotency_key
      runtime_job_dir
      replay_batch_index_path
      graph_order_fingerprint
      asset_universe_digest
      base_reserve_node_id
      risky_node_ids
  - rollout execution_profile is typed enough for Cajtucu paper V1:
      execution_backend_id
      cost_model_id
      allow_synthetic_direct_edges
      synthetic_edge_research_reason
      linear_transaction_cost_rate
      allow_partial_fills
      allow_negative_base_reserve
      equity_mismatch_tolerance
      equity_mismatch_fail_tolerance
      live_execution_allowed
  - synthetic direct edges require an explicit research reason.
  - allow_partial_fills=true is refused until Runtime replay forwards it.
  - cost_model_id must be linear_transaction_cost_rate.v1.

V2.3:
  - prepare is target-dispatch oriented.
  - target_id is canonical.
  - requested_mode is plan|dry_run|execute.
  - plan does not call Runtime.
  - dry_run calls Runtime dry-run.
  - execute requires dry-run gate and Runtime policy permission.
  - replay/rollout intent routes to hero.marshal.rollout.
  - artifact_validation routes to inspect.
  - policy_training remains reserved until a finite Runtime contract exists.

V2.4:
  - inspect canonical public fields:
      fact_family_id
      fact_digest
      fact_digest_prefix
      fact_index
      component_family_id
  - old public aliases are rejected:
      family
      fact_family
      digest
      digest_prefix
      index
      component
  - subject=facts validates modes summary|lineage|preview.

V2.5a/V2.5b:
  - status and inspect expose the shared read-only operator envelope.
  - prepare and rollout expose the dispatch/delegation envelope supplement.
  - public packets now expose:
      schema_version
      refusal_reasons
      warnings
      next_safe_actions
      authority
      observed
      evidence_refs
      digests
  - top-level legacy next_action was removed from prepare/rollout operator
    packets.
  - target-driver iteration records may still carry next_action as historical
    ledger evidence, not as the top-level operator command field.

V2.6:
  - live --help documents status, prepare, rollout, and inspect.
  - rollout help uses requested_mode=plan|execute and labels plan examples as
    plan.
  - README and ROADMAP use next_safe_actions for public operator guidance.

