Live tool catalog excerpt
-------------------------
From:
  /cuwacunu/.build/hero/hero_marshal.mcp --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --list-tools-json

Public tools:

  hero.marshal.status
    Read-only Marshal health and authority-boundary summary: recent receipts,
    policy/advice visibility, refusal state, caller-supplied test surfaces,
    and explicit non-executor/non-proof flags.

  hero.marshal.prepare
    Prepare finite movement for one dispatchable Lattice target. Train/evaluate
    are the current target-movement path; replay uses rollout,
    artifact-readiness routes to inspect, and policy-training is reserved until
    a concrete Runtime contract exists.

  hero.marshal.rollout
    Prepare or execute a bounded Kikijyeba historical replay rollout from a
    completed Runtime job: policy set plus Cajtucu paper execution profile
    becomes Runtime replay trajectory evidence. Runtime executes and writes
    reports; Marshal records the handoff.

  hero.marshal.inspect
    Read-only evidence inspection. Subjects run, target, protocol, spawn,
    component, and facts explain Runtime/Lattice/Marshal state without
    execution, proof claims, checkpoint selection, policy selection, or writes.

Important public schema facts
-----------------------------
prepare:
  required:
    target_id
  requested_mode:
    plan | dry_run | execute
  drive_mode:
    one_step | budgeted
  additionalProperties:
    false

rollout:
  required:
    rollout_id
    rollout_attempt_id
    idempotency_key
    runtime_job_dir
    replay_batch_index_path
    requested_mode
    graph_order_fingerprint
    asset_universe_digest
    base_reserve_node_id
    risky_node_ids
  requested_mode:
    plan | execute
  execution_profile:
    additionalProperties=false
    fields:
      execution_backend_id
      cost_model_id
      allow_synthetic_direct_edges
      synthetic_edge_research_reason
      linear_transaction_cost_rate
      allow_partial_fills
      allow_negative_base_reserve
      equity_mismatch_tolerance
      equity_mismatch_fail_tolerance
      live_execution_allowed

inspect:
  required:
    subject
  subject:
    run | target | protocol | spawn | component | facts
  identity_mode:
    report | strict
  canonical fact fields:
    fact_family_id
    fact_digest
    fact_digest_prefix
    fact_index
  canonical component field:
    component_family_id
  additionalProperties:
    false

Live help excerpt
-----------------
From:
  /cuwacunu/.build/hero/hero_marshal.mcp --global-config /cuwacunu/src/config/.config --help

Marshal role and authority boundary:
  Marshal is a coordinator. It prepares bounded handoffs, checks request shape,
  records receipts, and explains evidence. Runtime Hero executes allowed
  waves/replay. Lattice Hero proves target satisfaction. Marshal does not
  become proof authority, market-readiness authority, deployment authority,
  checkpoint selector, or allocation authority.

hero.marshal.prepare:
  Purpose: prepare a bounded Runtime handoff for one Lattice target.
  requested_mode: plan, dry_run, or execute.
  Returns: target-driver packet, dispatchability/refusal reasons, optional
  Runtime dry-run handoff, and next safe actions.

hero.marshal.rollout:
  Purpose: prepare or execute a bounded historical replay rollout of a policy
  set against completed Runtime job artifacts.
  Core model:
    completed Runtime job + policy set + replay environment + Cajtucu paper
    execution profile -> Runtime replay report/evidence.
  requested_mode:
    plan or execute
  Returns:
    rollout plan in plan mode; in execute, Runtime replay handoff result
    digests and dispatch state. Runtime reports are written by Runtime;
    inspection summaries come from later inspect.

hero.marshal.inspect:
  Purpose: read-only operator inspection over Runtime/Lattice/Marshal evidence.
  Subjects:
    run
    target
    protocol
    spawn
    component
    facts

Key code excerpt: rollout contract
----------------------------------
File:
  src/include/kikijyeba/marshal/rollout_marshal.h

struct marshal_rollout_execution_profile_t {
  std::string schema_version{k_marshal_rollout_execution_profile_schema_v1};
  std::string execution_backend_id{"cajtucu.execution.paper.v1"};
  std::string cost_model_id{"linear_transaction_cost_rate.v1"};
  bool allow_synthetic_direct_edges{false};
  std::string synthetic_edge_research_reason{};
  double linear_transaction_cost_rate{0.0};
  bool allow_partial_fills{false};
  bool allow_negative_base_reserve{false};
  double equity_mismatch_tolerance{1.0e-6};
  double equity_mismatch_fail_tolerance{0.01};
  bool live_execution_allowed{false};
};

struct marshal_rollout_request_t {
  std::string schema_version{k_marshal_rollout_request_schema_v1};
  std::string rollout_id{};
  std::string rollout_attempt_id{};
  std::string idempotency_key{};
  std::string experiment_id{};
  std::filesystem::path config_path{"/cuwacunu/src/config/.config"};
  std::filesystem::path runtime_job_dir{};
  std::filesystem::path replay_batch_index_path{};
  std::filesystem::path runtime_exec_path{
      "/cuwacunu/.build/exec/cuwacunu_exec"};
  std::filesystem::path report_path{};
  std::string requested_mode{"plan"};
  std::string environment_mode{"historical_replay"};
  std::string environment_assembly_id{"kikijyeba.environment.replay.v1"};
  std::string graph_order_fingerprint{};
  std::string asset_universe_digest{};
  std::string base_reserve_node_id{};
  std::vector<std::string> risky_node_ids{};
  std::vector<std::string> policy_tokens{};
  std::int64_t max_steps{0};
  std::int64_t max_parallel_jobs{1};
  std::int64_t timeout_seconds{600};
  marshal_rollout_execution_profile_t execution_profile{};
  bool require_existing_runtime_job_dir{true};
  bool require_completed_runtime_job{true};
  bool require_replay_artifacts{true};
};

Validation highlights in validate_rollout_request:
  - missing rollout_id -> missing_rollout_id
  - missing rollout_attempt_id -> missing_rollout_attempt_id
  - missing idempotency_key -> missing_idempotency_key
  - requested_mode other than plan|execute -> unsupported_requested_mode
  - environment_mode other than historical_replay -> unsupported_environment_mode
  - environment_assembly_id other than kikijyeba.environment.replay.v1
    -> unsupported_environment_assembly_id
  - execution_backend_id other than cajtucu.execution.paper.v1
    -> unsupported_execution_backend_id
  - missing graph_order_fingerprint -> missing_graph_order_fingerprint
  - missing asset_universe_digest -> missing_asset_universe_digest
  - duplicate reserve in risky nodes -> base_reserve_node_duplicated_in_risky_nodes
  - duplicate risky nodes -> duplicate_risky_node_id
  - asset_universe_digest mismatch -> asset_universe_digest_mismatch
  - unsupported policy token -> unsupported_policy_token:<token>
  - unsupported cost_model_id -> unsupported_cost_model_id
  - synthetic edges enabled without reason -> missing_synthetic_edge_research_reason

